---
description: Keep documentation and READMEs accurate and updated
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- Whenever you receive a correction or correct a mistake, make sure it's documented in .cursor/rules either by updating an existing doc or adding a new one
- Whenever you make changes to a package, make sure its README stays up to date. READMEs should include:
  - A description of the package
  - Its responsibilities
  - Dependencies it has on other packages, or other packages on it
  - An architecture mermaid diagram
  - Links to relevant subsystem docs or ADRs
  - Any other context a developer needs when working in that package
- If you establish a new design decision, update the architecture docs in `docs/architecture docs`
